    "created_at": "2015-05-26T21:18:55Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-05-26T21:19:33Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "OK after a lengthy argument on IRC I guess we can't have this work properly, because we have (very questionable, architecture-wise) upgrade granting from Lua (as seen on the RA shellmap).\nThere are 3 possible ways IMO:\n- Have a proxy trait for granting upgrades from Lua, that would let us keep track of those uptrades (unlike the current situation).\n- Do the lint check and ignore Lua scripts. This will work for 99% of the maps, and give a few false warnings on the other 1% (not that big of a problem).\n- Do the lint check + a hacky \"check\" of any Lua scripts inside the map. That would actually work even for that 1%.\n"
  },
