    "updated_at": "2015-05-26T21:25:05Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Lua scripts are only part of the problem.  Pulling all of the possible upgrade sources in the game into one giant list to check against ignoring other metadata (such as warhead target filtering) means that you're going to get false negatives (linter accepting upgrade consumers that can never be triggered) too.\n\nProviding a per-actor list of external source types would also address that.\n"
